<script>
    StackExchange.ready(function () {

        var location = 0;
        if ($("body").hasClass("questions-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("question-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("faq-page")) {
            location = 5;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("home-page")) {
            location = 3;;
        }

        $('#tell-me-more').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: 'cta', location: location }, true);
            });
        });
        $('#herobox #close').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: "minimize", location: location }, true);
            });
            $.cookie("hero", "mini", { path: "/", expires: 365 });
            $.ajax({
                url: "/hero-mini",
                success: function (data) {
                    $("#herobox").fadeOut("fast", function () {
                        $("#herobox").replaceWith(data);
                        $("#herobox-mini").fadeIn("fast");
                    });
                }
            });
            return false;
        });
    });

</script>    <script>
        StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
            StackExchange.gps.track("hero.show", { hero_type: "hero", location: 3 }, true);
        });
    </script>

    <div class="summary">
        
        <h3><a href="/questions/42518518/how-do-i-find-exactly-which-query-clauses-matched-for-each-solr-hit" class="question-hyperlink" title="Suppose I have a complex query which is composed of many clauses.

<script>
    StackExchange.ready(function () {

        var location = 0;
        if ($("body").hasClass("questions-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("question-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("faq-page")) {
            location = 5;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("home-page")) {
            location = 3;;
        }

        $('#tell-me-more').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: 'cta', location: location }, true);
            });
        });
        $('#herobox #close').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: "minimize", location: location }, true);
            });
            $.cookie("hero", "mini", { path: "/", expires: 365 });
            $.ajax({
                url: "/hero-mini",
                success: function (data) {
                    $("#herobox").fadeOut("fast", function () {
                        $("#herobox").replaceWith(data);
                        $("#herobox-mini").fadeIn("fast");
                    });
                }
            });
            return false;
        });
    });

</script>    <script>
        StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
            StackExchange.gps.track("hero.show", { hero_type: "hero", location: 3 }, true);
        });
    </script>

<script>
    StackExchange.ready(function () {

        var location = 0;
        if ($("body").hasClass("questions-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("question-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("faq-page")) {
            location = 5;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("home-page")) {
            location = 3;;
        }

        $('#tell-me-more').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: 'cta', location: location }, true);
            });
        });
        $('#herobox #close').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: "minimize", location: location }, true);
            });
            $.cookie("hero", "mini", { path: "/", expires: 365 });
            $.ajax({
                url: "/hero-mini",
                success: function (data) {
                    $("#herobox").fadeOut("fast", function () {
                        $("#herobox").replaceWith(data);
                        $("#herobox-mini").fadeIn("fast");
                    });
                }
            });
            return false;
        });
    });

</script>    <script>
        StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
            StackExchange.gps.track("hero.show", { hero_type: "hero", location: 3 }, true);
        });
    </script>

                (function(appendChild) {
                    Node.prototype.appendChild = function() {
                        var parent = this;
                        var newNode = arguments[0];
                        if (parent.nodeName === 'HEAD'
                            && newNode
                            && newNode.nodeName === 'SCRIPT'
                            && newNode.src) {
                            
                            window.setTimeout(function() {
                                var result = newNode.src.match(/^https:\/\/maps\.googleapis\.com\/maps\/api\/place\/js\/(\w+)Service\./i) || [];
                                var service = result[1];
                                if (service) {
                                    if (service === 'Autocompletion') service =  2;
                                    else if (service === 'Place') service = 1;
                                    else service = 0;
                                    StackExchange.using('gps', function() {
                                        StackExchange.gps.track('google_maps_places_api.call', { service: service });
                                    });
                                }
                            }, 0);
                        }
                        return appendChild.apply(this, arguments);
                    };
                })(Node.prototype.appendChild);

<script>
    StackExchange.ready(function () {

        var location = 0;
        if ($("body").hasClass("questions-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("question-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("faq-page")) {
            location = 5;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("home-page")) {
            location = 3;;
        }

        $('#tell-me-more').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: 'cta', location: location }, true);
            });
        });
        $('#herobox #close').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: "minimize", location: location }, true);
            });
            $.cookie("hero", "mini", { path: "/", expires: 365 });
            $.ajax({
                url: "/hero-mini",
                success: function (data) {
                    $("#herobox").fadeOut("fast", function () {
                        $("#herobox").replaceWith(data);
                        $("#herobox-mini").fadeIn("fast");
                    });
                }
            });
            return false;
        });
    });

</script>    <script>

            StackExchange.gps.track("hero.show", { hero_type: "hero", location: 3 }, true);

        <h3><a href="/questions/42519384/nstableview-drawing-buttons-in-cell-anomaly-they-shouldnt-be-there" class="question-hyperlink" title="I have an NSTableView that&#39;s populated programmatically...         <a href="/users/signup?ssrc=hero&amp;returnurl=%2fusers%2fstory%2fcurrent&amp;amp;utm_source=stackoverflow.com&amp;amp;utm_medium=dev-story&amp;amp;utm_campaign=signup-redirect" id="tell-me-more" class="button">Sign up</a>

<script>
    StackExchange.ready(function () {

        var location = 0;
        if ($("body").hasClass("questions-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("question-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("faq-page")) {
            location = 5;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("home-page")) {
            location = 3;;
        }

        $('#tell-me-more').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: 'cta', location: location }, true);
            });
        });
        $('#herobox #close').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: "minimize", location: location }, true);
            });
            $.cookie("hero", "mini", { path: "/", expires: 365 });
            $.ajax({
                url: "/hero-mini",
                success: function (data) {
                    $("#herobox").fadeOut("fast", function () {
                        $("#herobox").replaceWith(data);
                        $("#herobox-mini").fadeIn("fast");
                    });
                }
            });
            return false;
        });
    });

</script>    <script>
        StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
            StackExchange.gps.track("hero.show", { hero_type: "hero", location: 3 }, true);
        });
    </script>

<script>
    StackExchange.ready(function () {

        var location = 0;
        if ($("body").hasClass("questions-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("question-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("faq-page")) {
            location = 5;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("home-page")) {
            location = 3;;
        }

        $('#tell-me-more').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: 'cta', location: location }, true);
            });
        });
        $('#herobox #close').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: "minimize", location: location }, true);
            });
            $.cookie("hero", "mini", { path: "/", expires: 365 });
            $.ajax({
                url: "/hero-mini",
                success: function (data) {
                    $("#herobox").fadeOut("fast", function () {
                        $("#herobox").replaceWith(data);
                        $("#herobox-mini").fadeIn("fast");
                    });
                }
            });
            return false;
        });
    });

</script>    <script>
        StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
            StackExchange.gps.track("hero.show", { hero_type: "hero", location: 3 }, true);
        });

<script>
    StackExchange.ready(function () {

        var location = 0;
        if ($("body").hasClass("questions-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("question-page")) {
            location = 1;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("faq-page")) {
            location = 5;;
        } else if ($("body").hasClass("home-page")) {
            location = 3;;
        }

        $('#tell-me-more').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: 'cta', location: location }, true);
            });
        });
        $('#herobox #close').click(function () {
            StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
                StackExchange.gps.track("hero.action", { hero_action_type: "minimize", location: location }, true);
            });
            $.cookie("hero", "mini", { path: "/", expires: 365 });
            $.ajax({
                url: "/hero-mini",
                success: function (data) {
                    $("#herobox").fadeOut("fast", function () {
                        $("#herobox").replaceWith(data);
                        $("#herobox-mini").fadeIn("fast");
                    });
                }
            });
            return false;
        });
    });

</script>    <script>
        StackExchange.using("gps", function () {
            StackExchange.gps.track("hero.show", { hero_type: "hero", location: 3 }, true);
        });

    <div class="summary">
        
        <h3><a href="/questions/42521321/angular-2-w-typescript-code-splitting-by-dynamically-importing-angular-modules" class="question-hyperlink" title="The Idea:
I am working on a new architecture pattern for Angular 2, and I seemed to be stuck at an odd point. Lets say I have a core platform with 7 sub Angular modules I want to include into the core....">Angular 2 w/ TypeScript: Code Splitting by dynamically Importing Angular modules from a CDN into the core application</a></h3>
        <div class="tags t-angular2 t-typescript t-module t-lazy-loading t-systemjs">
            <a href="/questions/tagged/angular2" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;angular2&#39;" rel="tag">angular2</a> <a href="/questions/tagged/typescript" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;typescript&#39;" rel="tag">typescript</a> <a href="/questions/tagged/module" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;module&#39;" rel="tag">module</a> <a href="/questions/tagged/lazy-loading" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;lazy-loading&#39;" rel="tag">lazy-loading</a> <a href="/questions/tagged/systemjs" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;systemjs&#39;" rel="tag">systemjs</a>

                (function(appendChild) {
                    Node.prototype.appendChild = function() {
                        var parent = this;
                        var newNode = arguments[0];
                        if (parent.nodeName === 'HEAD'
                            && newNode
                            && newNode.nodeName === 'SCRIPT'
                            && newNode.src) {
                            
                            window.setTimeout(function() {
                                var result = newNode.src.match(/^https:\/\/maps\.googleapis\.com\/maps\/api\/place\/js\/(\w+)Service\./i) || [];
                                var service = result[1];
                                if (service) {
                                    if (service === 'Autocompletion') service =  2;
                                    else if (service === 'Place') service = 1;
                                    else service = 0;
                                    StackExchange.using('gps', function() {
                                        StackExchange.gps.track('google_maps_places_api.call', { service: service });
                                    });
                                }
                            }, 0);
                        }
                        return appendChild.apply(this, arguments);
                    };
                })(Node.prototype.appendChild);
